---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy — The F.A.M. Project" description="Privacy Policy for The FAM Project, Inc. Learn how we collect, use, and protect your personal information.">
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 prose prose-gray prose-headings:text-fam-purple prose-a:text-fam-green hover:prose-a:text-fam-purple-soft">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-fam-purple mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8"><strong>Effective Date: April 1, 2026</strong></p>

      <p>Welcome to <strong>The FAM Project, Inc. ("Company," "we," "our," or "us")</strong>, located at <a href="https://www.thefamproject.com">www.thefamproject.com</a>.</p>
      <p>We respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information.</p>

      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>We may collect the following categories of personal information:</p>

      <h3>A. Information You Provide</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Name, email address, phone number</li>
        <li>Mailing/billing address</li>
        <li>Payment information (processed via secure third-party providers)</li>
        <li>Account login credentials</li>
        <li>Information submitted through forms, surveys, or promotions</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>B. Automatically Collected Information</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>IP address</li>
        <li>Browser/device information</li>
        <li>Cookies and tracking technologies</li>
        <li>Usage data and interaction behavior</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>C. Sensitive Information</h3>
      <p>We <strong>do not intentionally collect sensitive personal data</strong> (such as SSN) unless explicitly required and disclosed.</p>

      <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p>We use your information to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Provide, operate, and improve our platform (FamCentral, WeR1, etc.)</li>
        <li>Process transactions and subscriptions</li>
        <li>Personalize your experience</li>
        <li>Communicate updates, offers, and promotions</li>
        <li>Provide customer support</li>
        <li>Ensure security and prevent fraud</li>
        <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Cookies &amp; Tracking Technologies</h2>
      <p>We use cookies and similar technologies to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Enhance user experience</li>
        <li>Analyze traffic and usage</li>
        <li>Support marketing and retargeting</li>
      </ul>
      <p>You can control cookies through your browser settings.</p>

      <h2>4. Sharing of Information</h2>
      <p>We <strong>do not sell personal data</strong>.</p>
      <p>We may share information with:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Service providers (payment processors, hosting, analytics)</li>
        <li>Marketing and affiliate partners within the FAM ecosystem</li>
        <li>Legal authorities when required</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Data Rights (CPRA, GDPR-Style Rights)</h2>
      <p>Depending on your location, you may have rights to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Access your data</li>
        <li>Correct inaccurate data</li>
        <li>Delete your data</li>
        <li>Opt-out of data sharing or marketing</li>
        <li>Limit use of sensitive information</li>
      </ul>
      <p>To exercise rights, contact us using the details below.</p>

      <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>We retain your information only as long as necessary to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Provide services</li>
        <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
        <li>Resolve disputes</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>7. Data Security</h2>
      <p>We implement:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>SSL encryption</li>
        <li>Secure payment gateways</li>
        <li>Restricted data access</li>
      </ul>
      <p>However, no system is 100% secure.</p>

      <h2>8. Third-Party Links</h2>
      <p>Our platform may contain links to third-party sites. We are not responsible for their privacy practices.</p>

      <h2>9. Children's Privacy (COPPA)</h2>
      <p>We do not knowingly collect data from children under 13.</p>

      <h2>10. SMS &amp; Communications</h2>
      <p>By providing your phone number, you consent to receive:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Transactional messages</li>
        <li>Promotional messages (if opted in)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>You may opt out anytime by replying: <strong>STOP, END, or QUIT</strong></p>
      <p>Message/data rates may apply.</p>

      <h2>11. Email Communications (CAN-SPAM Compliance)</h2>
      <p>We comply with CAN-SPAM and:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Do not use misleading subject lines</li>
        <li>Provide clear opt-out options</li>
        <li>Honor unsubscribe requests promptly</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>12. AI &amp; Data Usage Disclosure (2026 Standard)</h2>
      <p>We may use data to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Improve platform intelligence</li>
        <li>Enhance personalization</li>
        <li>Develop features powered by AI</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do <strong>not use personal data to train external AI systems without consent</strong>.</p>

      <h2>13. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this policy periodically. Updates will be posted on this page with a new effective date.</p>

      <h2>14. Contact Information</h2>
      <p>For questions regarding this Privacy Policy, contact:</p>
      <p>
        <strong>The FAM Project, Inc.</strong><br />
        222 S. Mill Ave Flr 8 Ste 80, Tempe, AZ 85281<br />
        <a href="mailto:help@thefamproject.com">help@thefamproject.com</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
